                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="91541" author="rread" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 16:58:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The tests only use pdsh based on the configuration, so that should not be dependency.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="91540" author="bogl" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 16:49:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wonder if this is a rathole we want to go down at all.  I think our -tests package implicitly requires a whole host of things not mentioned as dependencies.  pdsh and a bunch of other stuff from our tools build come to mind immediately.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="91538" author="rread" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 16:35:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Right, the dependencies should be on the -tests package. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please also add a dependency on  &quot;lsof&quot; which I noticed recently was used by llmountcleanup.sh but not included in the package dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="91537" author="mdiep" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 16:35:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;here is the patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/11433/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/11433/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="91536" author="bogl" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2014 16:31:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;if needed by tests shouldn&apos;t it be lustre-client-tests rpm with the dependency, not lustre-client?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
